{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"46846b9b-d25d-4f7d-9dc5-f1d4057c2bc4","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a built-in .NET MAUI property — that's likely why it has no effect. Here's what you actually need:\n\n**On iOS**, set the platform-specific flag on your page:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n```\n\n**On the Image/Layout**, set `IgnoreSafeArea` — this is what actually lets content extend behind system bars:\n\n```xml\n<Image Source=\"photo.jpg\"\n       Aspect=\"AspectFill\"\n       IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\" />\n```\n\n**On Android (.NET 10)**, apps targeting Android 15+ are edge-to-edge by default. If you're on an older target, enable it in your `MainActivity`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n    AndroidX.Core.View.WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n}\n```\n\n**TL;DR:** The two key things you're missing are `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` on the page and `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on the Image itself.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"48d7bc14-da57-4b1c-a0cf-76a43eab467e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about making content go edge-to-edge in a .NET MAUI app, going behind the status bar and navigation bar. They've tried `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but still see padding.\n\nThis is a common .NET MAUI question. The key issue is that in .NET MAUI, to go truly edge-to-edge, you need to:\n\n1. Set `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on the view/layout itself\n2. On Android, you may need to handle the edge-to-edge display differently\n3. The `SafeAreaEdges` property on ContentPage controls which edges respect safe areas on iOS\n\n\n4. On iOS, you can also use the platform-specific `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` property, and on Android you need to configure the window for edge-to-edge rendering\n\n, which is the default behavior in newer .NET MAUI versions targeting Android 15+.\n\nThe real issue is likely that `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` needs to be applied directly to the Image or its parent layout, not just the page level, and on iOS the `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` directive should handle the safe area insets. Since the user is on .NET 10, Android edge-to-edge should work out of the box, so I should focus on the layout-level property and the iOS-specific setting.","outputTokens":1019,"requestId":"77F5:36525B:186BCC:1D0E50:69EAC0A7"},"id":"265aee3c-4e21-4e23-b316-31f04aaac9ae","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:00:44.170Z","parentId":"27515abc-6930-48e0-9f4a-d2558e564587"}
